    "description": "Provenance REQ: jn70zc9m0vfsxrwv8smne7kxt583vnwz\n\nPR_SET_PDEATHSIG set on child before exec ensures child receives SIGTERM if noscope dies (SIGKILL, crash, OOM). Process group kill on exit ensures grandchildren are also terminated. Linux-specific, defense-in-depth on top of TTL. Does not apply to mint mode.\n\nRules:\n- NS-024: Process group management in run mode — PR_SET_PDEATHSIG on child; create new process group; kill entire group on exit; prevents orphaned grandchildren retaining credentials\n\nProvenance stats: 0 resolutions, 1 rule",
